ve important implications for environmental resources eg water nitrogen and land implications which are often hidden by the complex nature of global trade projects globalization trade and the environment the case of brazil fsi stanford fse project agricultural lives of the poor fsi stanford fse project completed consequences of increased global meat consumption on the global environment trade in virtual water and nutrients fsi stanford fse project completed integrated studies of sustainability land water systems of the yaqui basin fsi stanford fse project completed publications cover sugar and ethanol production as a rural development strategy in brazil evidence from the state of sao paulo luiz martinelli rachael garrett silvio ferraz rosamond l naylor agricultural systems vol 104 5 2011 html+ cover trading carbon for food global comparison of carbon stocks vs crop yields on agricultural land holly gibbs proceedings of the national academy of sciences vol 107 44 2010 html+ cover tropical forests were the primary source of new agricultural land in the 1980s and 1990s holly gibbs as ruesch f achard mk clayton p holmgren n ramankutty ja foley proceedings of the national academy of sciences vol 107 37 2010 html+ cover nutrient imbalances in agricultural development peter vitousek rosamond l naylor et al science vol 324 2009 html+ cover enhancing productivity on suburban dairy farms in china hengyun ma allan rae jikun huang scott rozelle agricultural economics vol 37 1 2007 html+ search fse search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages research news farmer networks key to agricultural innovation in developing countries june 2 2011 fsi stanford fse news fse senior fellow scott rozelle on china's ability to meet increasing demand fsi stanford fse in the news kfgo on february 17 2011 new fse publication examines the impacts costs and opportunities for sustainable agriculture in brazil december 2 2010 fsi stanford fs